Hey Mary,

I totally agree with you about indoor skydiving - I've heard it's a great way to get a taste of the real thing. And speaking of adrenaline-pumping activities, have you ever gone ziplining? I went for the first time a few months ago and it was absolutely thrilling - the views were incredible!

As for VR experiences, have you ever tried the one that combines bungee jumping and high-speed car chases in the Swiss Alps? I've been reading up on it and it sounds like an adrenaline junkie's dream come true.

Another sport I'm interested in trying is bouldering. I've heard it's a great workout and a lot of fun. Plus, I'm always up for a new challenge!

John

